On Mon, 18 Aug 2003, Thomas J. Tarka wrote:

> don't discount a loose head as the cause for this.  then again, i've never
> had a valve go.

If a valve gets damaged and the head of the valve breaks away from the
stem, it'll destroy the piston, allowing the conn rod to run loose in the
cylinder - I've had it happen at least once in the old days. The receding
valve seat symptom is a sign of something wrong, possibly overheating of
that cylinder, which could lead to the above.
OKAY:
