They both look normal, which is wierd considering all symptoms.

My timing at full advance is 27 degrees, using a good quality KAL Advance
timing light, with low hours of use. I think it should be at 30, I'll set
it at 30 - any opinions are welcome here.

As I've stated before , my main concern is that loss of 4 mils (seat
recession on #3 exhaust), on #3 exhaust.

